channel.title: Server Syndicate HELP PLEASE!
channel.description:
Hey Guys! I have a server syndicate for my server and it helps to restart my server using CMD. I am able to got it working on my Computer but it wont work on my VPS. It will keep saying 'tasklist' is an unrecognise.. a typical java error and the time will go mad and decrease it a rapid pace. Anyone help me? Where is wrong?
Might Bean

item.title: Server Syndicate HELP PLEASE!
item.dc:creator: @Mighty_Bean Mighty Bean
item.description:
@Mighty_Bean wrote:

[quote=“Kaex, post:2, topic:377313”]I don’t really know lol.

I’m guessing you could try remove this file named ‘Tasklist’.

Or try edit it to your RVM / JDK

Or even then I heard you can install JDK / JVM into a VPS? I might be wrong but worth a try.[/quote]

No Bro, a Server Syndicate is a .bat file. There are no ‘tasklist’ file. I already got JDK / JVM on my VPS if not I could not even compile.

Anyone can help me with this? Thank You in advance

Mighty Bean
